{"TopicId":187358,"ForumId":109,"TopicTitle":"KSP 2 Multiplayer Discussion Thread","CreatedByName":"Johnster_Space_Program","CreatedById":187334,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-20T00:10:22Z","PageNum":36,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Lettuce","CreatedById":219466,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-04-11T13:35:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224115034\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187358\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221649683204\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022219348\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Vl3d\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 minutes ago, Vl3d said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFine, then set your journey maneuver nodes and target while you\u0027re on the launch pad. Auto-warp to the correct time window while on the ground - but outside of multiplayer. Launch for a direct encounter. You can cancel (revert to launch) to return to multiplayer.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAt this point you\u0027ve dropped so many parts of your original proposal that its becoming regular time warp the only time I\u0027m seeing that you can\u0027t use timewarp in this system with all of the amendments you\u0027ve made is essentially while landing which is a 4 minute inconvenience when parachuting on Kerbin for the sake of immersion. I\u0027m not trying to bash you so I apologize if that\u0027s how this post comes off but I hope you can see why so many players took issue with your original proposal.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vl3d","CreatedById":219348,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-04-11T13:45:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy initial proposal was to have a real-time MMO game. I have not compromised on this. Of course there are workarounds to give solutions to your comments and critiques.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s becoming more \u0026amp; more clear that a hybrid system is the way to go with syncing to the regional / celestial body / target real-time bubble instead of syncing to a certain players time bubble.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m advocating giving sync configuration control to the server instead of the player having time travel prerogatives.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis was my original idea, it has not changed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/213541-t_v/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022213541\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/213541-t_v/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@t_v\u003C/a\u003EQueued actions recorded while warping that are then replayed for other players are ok only if you leave the bubble for good and can\u0027t return to meet yourself and break causality.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222022-04-11T13:46:48Z\u0022 title=\u002204/11/2022 01:46  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00222 yr\u0022\u003EApril 11, 2022\u003C/time\u003E by Vl3d\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Guest","CreatedById":-1,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-04-11T13:49:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224115041\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187358\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221649684736\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022219348\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Vl3d\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, Vl3d said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have not compromised on this.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou contraddicted yourself so many times that I think that \u0022your proposal\u0022 is really at least a couple of different ones for each page of this discussion.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou started from \u0022no timewarp within a \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003ESOI\u003C/abbr\u003E\u0022 and now you\u0027re replying to me with a \u0022Easy, you just timewarp\u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vl3d","CreatedById":219348,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-04-11T14:09:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve really put in the effort to explain the system. \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/213541-t_v/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022213541\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/213541-t_v/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@t_v\u003C/a\u003Egets it. I\u0027ll update the Q\u0026amp;A with the new ideas and let\u0027s leave it at that for posterity. I hope we get massive real-time multiplayer. Very curious about the KSP2 teams technical decisions.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222022-04-11T14:10:26Z\u0022 title=\u002204/11/2022 02:10  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00222 yr\u0022\u003EApril 11, 2022\u003C/time\u003E by Vl3d\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Pthigrivi","CreatedById":105624,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-04-11T14:13:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOkay, without piling on I think I can help out here. What \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/219348-vl3d/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022219348\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/219348-vl3d/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Vl3d\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0is after is being able to see in real time what a bunch of other players around the world are doing around Kerbin, Duna, other systems, etc. Because he has it blocked off into separate agencies (smart) you aren\u0027t actually physically interacting with any of these stations and bases and vessels anyway, so there\u0027s no real threat of temporal paradox, which means you don\u0027t actually have to restrict time warp at all. In fact, you don\u0027t need to synch with them either. You can just preserve your and your agencies self-consistent timeline unto itself, never see big shifts in your calendar or in the positions of planets around you. When you arrive close to a new planet nothing changes for \u003Cem\u003Eyou\u003C/em\u003E, you can just load the positional tracks and models within visual range of other players as they are relative to the host planet. Since you\u0027re not interacting with them it doesn\u0027t matter that when they zoom out in map mode they see all the other planets in different places.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"t_v","CreatedById":213541,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-04-11T14:16:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI do get it even if I disagree with it.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe core of the solution is a real time \u201Ctrue time\u201D. Time warp and which times it is restricted is secondary, but what remains constant is what time players can be in during normal operations. Other solutions allow you to be at any \u201Ctrue time\u201D for each player while this one has one \u201Ctrue time\u201D per server-defined bubble. This is what is meant by real time.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224115053\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187358\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221649686437\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022105624\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Pthigrivi\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, Pthigrivi said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhen you arrive close to a new planet nothing changes for \u003Cem\u003Eyou\u003C/em\u003E, you can just load the positional tracks and models within visual range of other players as they are relative to the host planet. Since you\u0027re not interacting with them it doesn\u0027t matter that when they zoom out in map mode they see all the other planets in different places.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPretty much, but on top of that everyone sees the planets in the same positions, even if it is just visually (because you can warp to a transfer window). This is a lot of effort for a little bit of shared experience between players, but for some I guess it is worth it.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vl3d","CreatedById":219348,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-04-11T14:27:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s worth it because you get to see the ending of this in-game (and we all build and play in the same universe together and share crafts):\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022113\u0022 width=\u0022200\u0022 data-embed-src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/P_nj6wW6Gsc?feature=oembed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bej Kerman","CreatedById":182413,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-04-11T14:59:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224114839\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187358\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221649634404\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022219348\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Vl3d\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n15 hours ago, Vl3d said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt feels like cheating, breaks mini-games.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt isn\u0027t cheating at all, though, and there\u0027s no reason to be strict.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224115063\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187358\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221649687240\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022219348\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Vl3d\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n38 minutes ago, Vl3d said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s worth it because you get to see the ending of this in-game (and we all build and play in the same universe together and share crafts):\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou can\u0027t do that with the same system Luna Multiplayer uses? Of course you can. DMP and LMP already let you build and play and share crafts without the burdens introduced by having to all be in-sync. You don\u0027t need to sacrifice timewarp.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEither way, no amount of talking is going to convince me that making this, just this, possible (even though it already is with timewarp) is worth sacrificing timewarp.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224114859\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187358\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221649637330\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022199897\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DwightLee\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n14 hours ago, DwightLee said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwhen you Resync, someone is going to move in time and space...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhen you resync, your planets will move but no-one else\u0027s should.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222022-04-11T15:06:31Z\u0022 title=\u002204/11/2022 03:06  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00222 yr\u0022\u003EApril 11, 2022\u003C/time\u003E by Bej Kerman\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DwightLee","CreatedById":199897,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-04-11T16:04:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224115073\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187358\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221649689172\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022182413\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Bej Kerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Bej Kerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhen you resync, your planets will move but no-one else\u0027s should.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, planets will move, stations will move, craft will move anything that orbits over time will move. I would prefer a solution that does not have that issue.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bej Kerman","CreatedById":182413,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-04-11T16:17:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224115095\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187358\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221649693092\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022199897\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DwightLee\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n11 minutes ago, DwightLee said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224115073\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187358\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221649689172\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022182413\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Bej Kerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Bej Kerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhen you resync, your planets will move but no-one else\u0027s should.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, planets will move, stations will move, craft will move anything that orbits over time will move. I would prefer a solution that does not have that issue.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis isn\u0027t an issue in the first place. The planets only move\u00A0\u003Cem\u003Efor you.\u003C/em\u003E Removing timewarp to fix this (non-existent) \u0022issue\u0022 just leads to the much, much larger issue of there being no timewarp.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vl3d","CreatedById":219348,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-04-11T18:01:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Build-Fly-Dream-Together.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022127.75\u0022 height=\u0022968\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.ibb.co/bK25v2Q/Build-Fly-Dream-Together.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DwightLee","CreatedById":199897,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-04-11T18:11:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224115100\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187358\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221649693844\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022182413\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Bej Kerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Bej Kerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis isn\u0027t an issue in the first place. The planets only move\u00A0\u003Cem\u003Efor you.\u003C/em\u003E Removing timewarp to fix this (non-existent) \u0022issue\u0022 just leads to the much, much larger issue of there being no timewarp.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPlanets, stations, craft moving when you re-sync is indeed an issue if you do any planning ahead with your space program.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bej Kerman","CreatedById":182413,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-04-11T18:34:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224115179\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187358\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221649700706\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022199897\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DwightLee\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n22 minutes ago, DwightLee said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224115100\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187358\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221649693844\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022182413\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Bej Kerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Bej Kerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis isn\u0027t an issue in the first place. The planets only move\u00A0\u003Cem\u003Efor you.\u003C/em\u003E Removing timewarp to fix this (non-existent) \u0022issue\u0022 just leads to the much, much larger issue of there being no timewarp.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPlanets, stations, craft moving when you re-sync is indeed an issue if you do any planning ahead with your space program.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u